    "intro": "Interpretation moves from what the text says to what it means — tracing Samuel's intent in his original covenant context, and locating the chapter within the canonical argument of Samuel-Kings and the broader Old Testament theology of kingship, covenant, and prophetic office. The movements below follow the chapter's own three-part structure: Samuel's self-vindication, the historical covenant lawsuit, and the pastoral response to Israel's confession.",
